{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "08", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "13", "M": "56", "S": "35"}}, "news": [{"title": "Smartworks lease out over 400 seats to Japanese NBFC subsidiary in Mumbai", "para": "Smartworks Coworking Spaces has secured a significant deal, leasing over 400 seats to a Japanese NBFC subsidiary in Mumbai for a five-year term. This agreement is projected to generate \u20b935 crore in rental revenue, highlighting the company's success in catering to large enterprise clients who constitute a substantial portion of its income.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/smartworks-secures-35-crore-lease-with-japanese-nbfc-in-mumbai/131587636?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-96870/131587636.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "SC-appointed amicus curiae seeks direction to MCD on action taken against illegal constructions", "para": "Following a deadly building collapse in Delhi, an amicus curiae has urged the Supreme Court to direct the MCD to survey and act against illegal constructions. The court is asked to mandate structural audits, sealing, and demolition of unauthorized structures, and investigate how the collapsed building was allowed to continue construction despite multiple bookings.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/supreme-court-seeks-action-from-mcd-after-fatal-building-collapse-in-delhi/131587703?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2067238/131587703.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Bihar government set to launch paperless property registration system", "para": "Bihar is ushering in a fully paperless property registration system, a significant digital governance reform. This initiative, approved by the cabinet, aims to boost transparency and efficiency in land transactions. Buyers and sellers will soon complete the entire process online using digital signatures and Aadhaar authentication, eliminating the need for physical documents. The phased rollout begins this month.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/technology/bihar-government-set-to-launch-paperless-property-registration-system/131588850?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2063241/131588850.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "technology"}]}